cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO 

The paper proposes a novel model for 3D semantic completion from a single depth image, which involves computer vision (CV) and graphics (GR) techniques. The model uses a single encoder and three separate generators, which are trained using a limited amount of real data, indicating the use of machine learning (LG) and artificial intelligence (AI) methods. Finally, the paper demonstrates the benefits of the proposed approach on standard benchmarks for 3D object completion, which suggests the use of robotics (RO) applications.
